PROJECT
Correctional Facility Environmental Sensor Analytics Platform

This data comes from gateway which is available in prison/facilities etc.
From gateway we get multiple type of data like wrist watch data, waterleak, temp-senosr in the form of 02010613FF3906CA03201C2D0380008000800047F8321E and from it we get desirable Data for any type of sensors like watch,temp, weater leak etc this value is rssi

GOAL
Build a scalable AWS-based system that processes real-time sensor readings received in Lambda every 5–10 seconds and generates:

- real-time analytics
- anomaly detection
- temperature forecasting
- operational alerts

The system must support:

- multi-tenant clients
- lightweight ML models
- single deployment serving multiple clients
- dev / staging / production environments
- infrastructure as code
- CI/CD automation


=========================================================
CURRENT SYSTEM ENTRY POINT
=========================================================

Sensor devices publish data to AWS IoT Core.

AWS IoT triggers Lambda.

Lambda receives events every 5–10 seconds.

Example event received by Lambda:

{
 "timestamp": "2026-03-07T10:22:14Z",
 "device_id": "C30000301A80",
 "temperature": 82.7,
 "rssi": -62,
 "power": 87
}

Device ID is the primary identifier.

Facility/location metadata is optional and stored separately.


=========================================================
KEY DESIGN PRINCIPLES
=========================================================

1. Device-centric processing
Primary identifier is device_id.

2. Lightweight ML models
Models must be fast and low compute.

3. Multi-tenant system
Multiple clients share same infrastructure.

4. Config-driven client routing
Client logic determined by configuration.

5. Single deployment
One system serving all tenants.

6. Serverless architecture
Minimize infrastructure overhead.


